The paper focuses on identifying compromised mobile devices through network traffic analysis and graph inference. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with identifying compromised devices. The paper also involves network traffic analysis (cs.NI) and graph inference (cs.SI), which are closely related to the topic. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and graph-based inferences (cs.DS) to identify compromised devices.
